This may be specific to MacOS 11.0+, which we haven't adopted yet.

You can try unsetting the option to use the embedded DevTools inspector in Flutter preferences.
Thanks for reply. This is not blocking me currently. I just provide some information may be helpful.

I verified with the JxBrowser team that MacOS 11.0+ isn't supported yet. I expect this will be updated in their next release, or we can check for OS version and suggest opening DevTools in a separate browser for our next release.

I think this is what we should do for [M52](https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/milestone/64), scheduled for Dec 4:
- Check for MacOS 11, and if found
-- Disable the embedded DevTools option
-- Always use the Java inspector
- Be prepared to revert if JxBrowser updates to MacOS 11 by Dec 3.

The reason I think it should be in M52 is I suspect quite a few Mac-based Flutter devs will be switching earlier rather than later, and it isn't that much work.

@devoncarew may have an opinion, too.
